The second reason Democrats must not pursue impeachment is a simple example from recent history of the electoral consequences of attempting to impeach the sitting president.
Put another way, voters rejected the impeachment proceedings, as well as the character assault against the president, and swung him an important electoral victory.
Third, and possibly the most important reason, Democrats must not pursue impeachment proceedings because they will distract from the essential job of leading and legislating.
Another important policy area where Democrats must direct their focus, instead of pursuing impeachment, is prescription drug pricing reform.
The longer House Democrats push off the tough business of legislating and driving compromise on immigration, the longer these vulnerable communities will anguish.